  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?** (choose one): BUG REPORT\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version** (use `kubectl version`): 1.5\r\n\r\n\r\n**Environment**: Any juju deployed environment\r\n- **Cloud provider or hardware configuration**: Any cloud used by juju\r\n- **OS** (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Ubuntu 16.04.2 LTS\r\n- **Kernel** (e.g. `uname -a`): 4.4.0-66-generic\r\n- **Install tools**:\r\n- **Others**:\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nRemoved all kubernetes-master units and then re-added one master node and that master was failing.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe master would function properly.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible):\r\nRemove all kubernetes-master units and then re-added one master. There is also this tests that shows the issue: https://github.com/ktsakalozos/bundle-canonical-kubernetes/blob/bug/master-check/tests/40-remove-add-master-check.py\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know**:\r\nThis is for the deployments done with juju\r\n",
